<body>
<div class="container">

  <h1>Real Express Problems We Faced</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">Actual backend and Express.js runtime issues faced while using KeshavSoft npm modules and VS Code extensions.</p>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>1. AddSubRoute Command Not Found</h2>
    <div class="module">Extension: express api sub routes generate</div>
    <p>VS Code failed to detect the AddSubRoute command.</p>
    <pre>command 'extension.editor.title.addSubRoute' not found</pre>
    <p class="fix">Fix:</p>
    <p>Reload VS Code or reinstall extension correctly.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>2. Wrong Generated Import Path</h2>
    <div class="module">Module: @keshavsoft/kschema-api-gen</div>
    <p>After generating ShowAll API, Node.js failed to locate routes.js.</p>
    <pre>Cannot find module 'V1/routes.js'</pre>
    <p>Actual file existed inside: <code>Api/V1/routes.js</code></p>
    <p class="fix">Fix:</p>
    <pre>import { router } from "./Api/V1/routes.js";</pre>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>3. Default Export Error</h2>
    <div class="module">Module: ks-express-boilerplate</div>
    <p>app.js imported default export, but routes.js exported named router.</p>
    <pre>does not provide an export named 'default'</pre>
    <p class="fix">Fix:</p>
    <pre>export default router;
// OR use named import correctly</pre>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>4. Router Callback Required Error</h2>
    <div class="module">Modules: ks-express-boilerplate + express api generator + kschema-api-gen</div>
    <p>Invalid router object passed into app.use().</p>
    <pre>TypeError: argument callback is required</pre>
    <p class="fix">Fix:</p>
    <p>Correct router import/export structure.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>5. API Route Mounting Problem</h2>
    <div class="module">Module: express api generator</div>
    <p>Generated routes existed, but app.js was not connecting routes properly.</p>
    <p class="fix">Final Working Fix:</p>
    <pre>import { router as routerFromApi } from "./Api/routes.js";
app.use("/Api", routerFromApi);</pre>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>6. setupRoutes() vs app.use() Confusion</h2>
    <div class="module">Modules: ks-express-boilerplate + express api generator</div>
    <p>Both routing systems existed simultaneously.</p>
    <pre>setupRoutes(app);
app.use("/Api", routerFromApi);</pre>
    <p>This created confusion about route ownership.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>7. Wrong Working Directory</h2>
    <div class="module">Module: @keshavsoft/kschema-api-gen-actions</div>
    <p>Generators depended on <code>process.cwd()</code>. Running commands from the wrong folder generated incorrect structure and imports.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>8. Route Hierarchy Dependency</h2>
    <div class="module">Modules: express api generator + express api sub routes generate + express api endpoints generate + kschema-api-gen-actions</div>
    <p>Entire API flow depended on proper route chain:</p>
    <pre>app.js
  ↓
Api/routes.js
  ↓
Api/V1/routes.js
  ↓
Api/V1/journals/end-points.js</pre>
    <p>One broken import/export stopped the API completely.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>9. Automatic Import Updates</h2>
    <div class="module">Module: @keshavsoft/kschema-api-gen-actions</div>
    <p>npm generators automatically modified source files using:</p>
    <pre>updateImports.js
updateUse/index.js</pre>
    <p>This could create:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Wrong insertion position</li>
      <li>Broken imports</li>
      <li>Malformed routes</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>10. Duplicate Prevention Requirement</h2>
    <div class="module">Module: @keshavsoft/kschema-api-gen-actions</div>
    <p>Generator already contained <code>checkDuplicate.js</code> because repeated generation could create:</p>
    <pre>router.get('/ShowAll', ...)
router.get('/ShowAll', ...)</pre>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>11. end-points.js Auto Modification</h2>
    <div class="module">Module: @keshavsoft/kschema-api-gen-actions</div>
    <p>Action generators automatically updated <code>end-points.js</code>. Incorrect updates could break routing structure.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="problem">
    <h2>12. Boilerplate Generated But Runtime Failed</h2>
    <div class="module">Modules: ks-express-boilerplate + route generators</div>
    <p>Folder structure generated correctly:</p>
    <pre>Api/
V1/
journals/</pre>
    <p>But runtime still failed because:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Wrong imports</li>
      <li>Wrong exports</li>
      <li>Missing route linkage</li>
      <li>ESM module mismatch</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="conclusion">
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>These were real Express.js and backend problems faced while using:</p>
    <ul style="margin-top:12px">
      <li>ks-express-boilerplate</li>
      <li>express api generator</li>
      <li>express api sub routes generate</li>
      <li>express api endpoints generate</li>
      <li>@keshavsoft/kschema-api-gen</li>
      <li>@keshavsoft/kschema-api-gen-actions</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-top:16px">These issues helped us understand: Express route hierarchy, ESM imports and exports, automatic code generation, dynamic source code modification, and scalable backend architecture.</p>
  </div>

  <div style="margin-top:30px">
    <a class="back" href="index.html">← Back to Home</a>
  </div>

</div>
